<br>
Actually that part is not exactly true.  You got your starting Alignment when you generated your PC.  At Level 10 (or higher) you could change your Alignment ONE TIME ONLY to another Alignment that fit your Race/Class/Deity restrictions.<br>
<br>
So, under the old system you were allowed one 'change of heart' that could theoretically turn Good to Evil or vice versa.<br>
<br>
I will agree that this concept is a problem with defining RP purely on 'as stated' basis - there really isn't anything to stop say a Human character from switching between Good and Evil RP on a daily basis.  So obviously there is a lot of trust involved. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sirienfv>Sirien FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/03 11:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Side note</span><hr size=1> I don't RP all that often anymore ( I used to ALL the time), but if I come across someone who is RP'ing I'll RP with them.  Usually RP makes the game a more enjoyable experience, unless disputes like this arise.  <br>
<br>
I'm a wood elf ranger ranger and when we could choose alignments I picked discord neutral...which is borderline evil.  I can go either way really.  And as such I'm allied with of course Kelethin, Felwithe, but also with Neriak.  Well okay, not allied, but I can go in the place, use their bank, and talk to the females.  It makes me sick when dark elfs who are RP freaks classify me as 'lightbringer' and are unwilling to change their oppinion of me just because of my race.  I do have a storyline (which is made up of real in-game events...nothing was staged) and that storyline along with my in-game action, etc should be enough to allow me to hang with the evil ones...but often times they just can't get passed the fact that I'm a surface elf.  <br>
<br>
The truth is that my character is probably capable of more evil than any of the cursed children of Innoruuk because he IS allied with both, good and evil places...so if he felt like it, let's just say if we were RP'ing, he could start a war and play every side.  He could possibly align himself with both, good and evil players and just get what he needs from them.  Because of his unique neutrality, he has no cares about taking what he wants from whoever and in the end knows that the only one you need to take care of is yourself.  <br>
<br>
In my youth I used to call myself 'the dark ranger' , but even that never meant anything to most of the freak rp'ers.  It was &quot;oh, he's a lightbringer, he can't join us&quot;.  Then I'd tell them &quot;you mindless fools, if you were a worthy race you'd know that I am a dark ranger&quot;.  Still they didn't care.  And that's sad...RP works both ways...you have to accept other people's storylines too for things to work out.  Sure it still says I worship Tunare, and I don't claim to worship anyone else.  Tunare is the mother of all, not the mother of the good.  I'm supposed to protect nature, but the means with which I do that are all up to me.<br>
<br>
(Just a note here, I dont mean that every evil person I've met used to shun me because I was a surface elf...i mean, how do you think I got access to neriak?  I did have some really good DE friends who accepted me and my story and my attitude at the time.)  <br>
<br>
To me it just seems that a lot of people are not open-minded at all about the many aspects and ways one can RP.  And being as how I spent 40 some levels of my in-game life RP'ing I think that's terrible.  But like I said, I don't really find myself in too many RP situations anymore so I don't have to worry about all the insane made-up rules a lot of people have about how &quot;you MUST be an evil race to join us&quot; or &quot;your name isn't RP enough&quot; ...that's BS.  If someone has a name they like and they also try to RP, then don't hold them back because of their name...chances are they also have a storyline for their name.  And if you really treat this RP world like a 'real world' there are a lot of people in the real world with bazar names, but there's nothing you can do about it.  Maybe their parents were crack heads?  Who cares if you don't like their reasons for their name or don't like their story...it's their call and it's their character and this is never going to be a perfect rp world...same as the real world.  Just let everyone have fun.  <br>
<br>
But luckily I don't really have to put up with any of this nonsense anymore because I'm<br>
<br>
~Sirien<br>
60 Ranger<br>
The forever applicant of Fire and Fury<br>
<br>
I even almost hate to post this because someone probably won't agree with me, or they'll wonder what drugs I was on when I wrote this but everyone else was writing stuff and I wanted to write things too.  So I did.  So read it or ignore it.  Your call.  <br>
