<br>
Ah, you see, that is the rub.  The FV Alignment system (as well as the Sullon Zek one) are/were complete fabrications.  They ONLY ONLY ONLY had any meaning to Players.<br>
<br>
The world of Norrath in the game of EQ, was designed around the FACTION system.  Base factions are determined by Race/Class/Deity and could be modified through killing monsters or completing quests.<br>
<br>
As a Wizard of Sol Ro starting out when the server began, I could be Neutral Good or Neutral Evil.  But NO NPC in the game would perceive or respect that alignment.  All it affected was which PLAYERS I could group with.<br>
<br>
As an Erudite Wizard of Sol Ro, I would say that the world of Norrath perceives me as Neutral.  I started out KOS only in Ogguk, Grobb, Cabilis and Paineel.  I still have the Dubious faction I started with with Dark Elves and Barbarians.  I'm actually Ally with Paineel now because I've killed so many Kobolds I can't give that faction away, even though I've killed many a Heretic.  So I just RP it that they respect me out of fear.<br>
<br>
I have always played my character closer to Order Neutral, which is the alignment I would have had if it were an option (Sol Ro followers cannot be Ordered under the old system).<br>
<br>
I fight for truth and the interests of Erudin.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think too much emphasis is put of 'Good' and 'Evil.'  I think the Racial/Factional considerations are more compelling.  Elves and Tier'dal don't get along because of their very nature - each is a twisted mockery of the other.  Tier'dal and Halflings are enemies because they are neighboring states at war  -- Even if there are Good DEs and Evil Halflings, in general the two societies don't get along.<br>
<br>
Where people get tripped up, is on the game mechanics - Particular Race/Class/Deity combos that are mandatory or impossible.  Prexus is available to very few characters is it that awful for someone wanting to RP being a Prexus follower... Or Veeshan follower or whatever?<br>
<br>
The number one complaint I have seen to Verant regarding RP is 'Let us change our Religions!'  --  Yet the same people adamantly refuse to let anyone simply RP such a change, as if that word on their character sheet which is INVISIBLE to everyone is the most important thing in the world. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bakanome>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/03 3:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Side note</span><hr size=1> The only situation where I honestly say a character cannot possibly be the opposite of their alignment would be the redeemed necromancer/shadowknight or the fallen paladin.  There is no way any of these classes could possibly switch around their powers.  Tunare, Rodcet, Erollsi and Mithaniel Marr would never allow necromantic magics to pervert creation in that way (although Brell may) and Innoruuk sure as hell ain't going to let a person go around curing people of illness, being valorous and Laying Hands.<br>
<br>
A dark elf warrior, cleric, or anything like that of Tunare, I can see.  A dark elf shadowknight?  It's not even remotely consistant.  Same goes for high elves and their paladins.<br>
<br>
Basically, I'll believe your story as long as it makes sense.  Paladins of Innoruuk, necromancers/shadowknights of Tunare/Marr/Nife?  No, it doesn't even make sense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sinchyld>sinchyld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Dark Prince</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/03 3:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.e2-online.net/eq/ezboard_dom.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Side note</span><hr size=1> $12.95 from my account means it doesnt have to make sense to anyone but me.<br>
