</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fajon>Fajon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warpriest<br>
Prime Nightmare </span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/03 4:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=70>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.ameritech.net/users/fatjohn/Emblem.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drama</span><hr size=1>                ~~Several concepts here~~<br>
<br>
A defined ruleset of who can and can't be evil promotes a stress free recruiting enviroment.  (This has been said earlier I know but I wanted to expand on it a little)  Who wants to waste a ton of game hours debating with someone's evilness.  I sure as hell do not.  If you want to do that sort of thing...more power to you.  If that type of RP does not fit with mine expect me to react in character from my characters view point.  It's that simple, a high elf walks up and tells my char they are evil...my char will laugh in their face.  <br>
<br>
There is no right or wrong here, but if you decide to create a RP that is contadictory to your born people's it creates a situation.  You have chosen to step outside the basic game outline, fine...just because you did does not mean that my character is going to accept you for what you say you are.<br>
<br>
~Dick Tracy walks into a bar, Pruneface and the boys are having a big mob meeting in the back.  Dick walks right up and says &quot;Hi guys, I am a mobster now too! Can I sit in?&quot;~<br>
<br>
Yeah right Dick Tracy<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
Another note ~ RP can only simulate RL to a certain degree.  If someone wanted to prove their evilness they could be tested.<br>
~&quot;Ok if you're so evil, go stick your blade in that old ladies eye.~<br>
No amount of faction work with her family is going to make them come to love you.  Forgive...maybe, love...somehow I don't think so.  In game there is no proof as to your evilness because anything done can be undone.<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
I know this is long...here is my wrap up<br>
<br>
This is just a big mess and colossal waste of time to me.  Being a game I accept certain limitations such as rules and guidelines.  Even as such I will always respond to your chosen RP with a RP consistent with my char.  So if you my char doesn't like yours or the reverse, step away and I will do the same.  Them not liking or accepting each other is STILL RP and there is no reason why it cannot be treated as such.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=464072"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/fatjohn/Warpriest.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosfuil>rosfuil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/03 5:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=71>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.rainweaver.com/EQ/Rose/Images/bounce.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drama</span><hr size=1> But but but Fajon, that makes sense.<br>
